  "texts": [
    "The abbreviations of the measurements are in the note of Table 4.Among the five RCTs, only the intervention group in Krämer et al. [37] reported a significant decrease in depressive symptoms, as well as improvements in psychological symptoms and quality of life, compared to the control group.",
    "In the other four RCTs, three Out of the five included RCTs, four had low risk and one had some concern with regard to the randomization process (due to significant baseline differences between two groups).",
    "Two studies had low risk and three has some concerns regarding low intervention adherence.Regarding missing data, two studies had low risk and three had moderate to high risk due to dropouts.",
    "All five studies had some concerns due to it being unclear if the assessment method was double blinded or not.",
    "Lastly, all studies had low risk of bias regarding the selection of the reported result."
  ]
}